## Why This Phase Changes Everything

```
Phases 0-4 taught you to BUILD infrastructure.
Phase 5 teaches you to KNOW if it's working.

Without observability:
  "Is the system healthy?" вҶ’ "I think so? Nobody's complained yet."
  "What caused the outage?" вҶ’ "We're not sure. Let's check the logs... 
                                which logs? There are 200 services."
  "Are we meeting our reliability targets?" вҶ’ "What targets?"

With observability:
  "Is the system healthy?" вҶ’ "SLO compliance is 99.97%, error budget 
                               has 4.2 hours remaining this month."
  "What caused the outage?" вҶ’ "Trace ID abc123 shows 2.3s latency at 
                                payment-service вҶ’ db query, correlating 
                                with CPU throttling on pod payment-7f8b."
  "Are we meeting our reliability targets?" вҶ’ Dashboard. One glance. Done.

At NovaMart:
  $50K/minute outage cost Г— average 15 minutes to detect without monitoring
  = $750K per incident in DETECTION DELAY ALONE
  
  With proper observability: detection in <2 minutes
  Savings: $650K per incident
```

