## 2. Prometheus вҖ” Architecture Deep Dive

### Why Prometheus Won

```
Before Prometheus (2012-2015):
  Nagios:   Host-level checks, polling, terrible scaling, config is XML hell
  Zabbix:   Better than Nagios, still agent-based, rigid schema
  Graphite: Metrics storage + graphing, push-based, no alerting
  StatsD:   Metrics aggregation, no storage, no querying
  
  Problems:
  - No dimensional data model (can't filter by label)
  - Push-based (services push metrics вҶ’ requires discovery + registration)
  - Poor K8s integration (designed for static servers, not ephemeral pods)
  - No native alerting with silencing/routing

Prometheus (2015+, CNCF graduated):
  вң“ Pull-based (Prometheus scrapes targets вҖ” works with K8s service discovery)
  вң“ Dimensional data model (labels: {service="order", region="us-east-1"})
  вң“ PromQL (powerful query language)
  вң“ Native alerting (Alertmanager with routing, silencing, grouping)
  вң“ K8s-native (ServiceMonitor CRDs, auto-discovery)
  вң“ Ecosystem (thousands of exporters, Grafana integration)
  вң“ Battle-tested at scale (SoundCloud, DigitalOcean, CERN, NovaMart)
```

