## Part 3: Correlation вҖ” Connecting Metrics вҶ” Logs вҶ” Traces

This is what separates observability from "three separate tools":

```
Incident: order-svc p99 latency spike
в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ

Step 1: METRICS (Prometheus/Grafana)
  вҶ’ See p99 spike on Golden Signals dashboard
  вҶ’ histogram_quantile(0.99, ...) jumped from 200ms to 5s at 14:32
  вҶ’ Annotation shows deployment at 14:30 вҖ” suspect!
  
Step 2: LOGS (Loki via Grafana)
  вҶ’ Click "Split" view, switch to Loki
  вҶ’ {app="order-svc", level="error"} | json | duration > 2s
  вҶ’ See: "database connection timeout" with traceID=abc123
  
Step 3: TRACES (Tempo/Jaeger via Grafana)
  вҶ’ Click traceID link вҶ’ opens trace view
  вҶ’ Trace shows: order-svc вҶ’ db-proxy вҶ’ RDS
  вҶ’ db-proxy span: 4.8s (normally 50ms)
  вҶ’ Root cause: RDS failover happened at 14:31, connection pool stale
  
Step 4: FIX
  вҶ’ Restart connection pool / configure connection validation
  вҶ’ Latency recovers at 14:45
```

**This correlation flow is configured in the datasource config** (shown above in the Grafana section):
- Prometheus вҶ’ Loki: via shared labels (`app`, `namespace`)
- Loki вҶ’ Tempo: via `derivedFields` (regex extracting traceID from log lines)
- Tempo вҶ’ Prometheus: via `tracesToMetrics` (service name mapping)

